==English==

===Etymology===
from French ''communiqué'' 'something communicated' (past participle of ''[[communiquer]]'' 'to communicate')

===Pronunciation===
IPA: /kəˌmjuːnɪˈkeː/

===Noun===
'''communiqué'''
#an official report or statement, such as a government [[press release]] or the report of a conference
#*The final communiqué of the G8 summit didn't even mention human rights.

